						<summary>

						<p>Māsti stone set up near Toṭada Vīraṇṇa temple.</p>						

						<p>1438 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This inscription is dated in Śaka 1360, (in words) Kāḷayukta, Śrāvaṇa ba. 10, Thursday and corresponds to A.D. 1438, August 14, Thursday f.d.t. 50.</p>						

						<p>It records the death of the bride of Mākagauḍa, son of Kōṭagāṟa-nayaka by ascending the funeral pyre (by the rite of <hi rend="italic">sahagamana</hi>) of her husband.</p>						

						</summary>
